---
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import BeLayout from '@/layouts/BeLayout.astro';
import leighTree from '@/assets/images/breathe/leigh-ancient-tree.jpg';
import leighHeadshotWarm from '@/assets/images/be/leigh-headshot-warm.jpg';
import stoneSpiral from '@/assets/images/be/leigh-stone-spiral.jpg';

const tools = [
  'ICF-accredited coaching methodology (She Leads, formerly The Clique Method)',
  'Yoga philosophy and somatic practice',
  'Yoga Nidra and guided meditation',
  'Mindfulness and nervous system awareness',
  'Tarot as a reflective and intuitive tool',
  'Ayurvedic principles',
  'Mahayana Buddhist philosophy',
  'Practical experience in the tech industry',
];
---

<BeLayout
  title="Coaching Approach & Method | Leigh Bertelsen"
  description="Coaching rooted in self-inquiry, yoga philosophy, somatic practice, and tarot. ICF-accredited through She Leads."
>
  <div class="page">

    {/* ── Opening ────────────────────────────────────────── */}
    <section class="intro" aria-label="Introduction">
      <p class="be-hero-quote">
        I’m not a “here’s your five-step plan” kind of coach.
      </p>
      <p class="body">
        What I’ve found, both in my own practice and working with clients,
        is that most of us already know what we need. The work is in
        creating enough stillness to hear it.
      </p>
    </section>

    <Image
      src={leighHeadshotWarm}
      alt="Leigh Bertelsen smiling warmly in a hotel lounge in Copenhagen"
      widths={[400, 800]}
      sizes="(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 500px"
      class="method-photo"
    />

    {/* ── Self-inquiry as the engine ─────────────────────── */}
    <section class="section" aria-label="The approach">
      <p class="section-label">the approach</p>
      <h2 class="section-title">Self-inquiry as the engine</h2>
      <p class="body">
        My coaching is rooted in the belief that you are your own greatest source of wisdom.
        The techniques I draw from are a unique mix: ICF-accredited coaching methodology,
        mindfulness practice, yoga philosophy, somatic awareness, and tarot as a reflective tool.
        They are all designed to help you access what's already there. I ask questions. You find the
        answers.
      </p>
      <p class="body">
        What this means in practice: you won't leave a session with a rigid action plan
        you'll quietly abandon. You'll leave with one or two things that feel genuinely
        doable, and a clearer sense of why they matter to you. As one client put it: the
        techniques center you as the source of clarity.
      </p>
    </section>

    <figure class="atmospheric-photo">
      <Image
        src={stoneSpiral}
        alt="Top-down view of a stone spiral path with autumn leaves underfoot."
        widths={[400, 700]}
        sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 70vh"
      />
      <figcaption>a stone spiral, autumn.</figcaption>
    </figure>

    {/* ── What a session feels like ──────────────────────── */}
    <section class="section" aria-label="In practice">
      <p class="section-label">in practice</p>
      <h2 class="section-title">What a session feels like</h2>
      <p class="body">
        We start with where you are, not where you think you should be. Sessions are
        conversational, not clinical. I listen carefully, ask questions that might surprise
        you, and follow what's actually present rather than a fixed agenda.
      </p>
      <p class="body">
        This approach is particularly useful if you have a lot to juggle at once: work,
        personal life, the part of yourself that keeps getting pushed to the bottom of the
        list. We make space for all of it.
      </p>
    </section>

    {/* ── The tools ──────────────────────────────────────── */}
    <section class="section" aria-label="What I draw from">
      <p class="section-label">what I draw from</p>
      <h2 class="section-title">The tools</h2>
      <ul class="tools-list" role="list">
        {tools.map((t) => <li class="tools-item">{t}</li>)}
      </ul>
    </section>

    {/* ── Background ─────────────────────────────────────── */}
    <section class="section" aria-label="Credentials">
      <p class="section-label">credentials</p>
      <h2 class="section-title">Background</h2>
      <p class="body">
        I completed my coach training through She Leads, an ICF-accredited programme. I
        hold a 500-hour yoga teacher certification through the Himalayan Institute, a Yoga
        Nidra Teacher certification, and an Ayurveda Yoga Specialist certification. I've
        studied contemplative practice seriously for over a decade, including time at Kopan
        Monastery in Nepal, Tushita Meditation Centre in Dharamshala, and Gomde in Austria.
        I've been reading tarot for 25 years.
      </p>
      <p class="body">
        I also work as a senior web developer, which means I understand exactly what it's
        like to be in a demanding technical role, to be the only person in the room thinking
        the way you think, and to wonder whether this is actually what you want.
      </p>
    </section>

    <Image
      src={leighTree}
      alt="Leigh Bertelsen sitting by an ancient tree beside a turquoise lake in Laos"
      widths={[400, 800]}
      sizes="(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 500px"
      class="method-photo method-photo-landscape"
    />

    {/* ── Podcast ────────────────────────────────────────── */}
    <section class="section" aria-label="Podcast">
      <p class="section-label">also worth a listen</p>
      <h2 class="podcast-title">Wellness and Women in Tech</h2>
      <p class="body">
        A podcast about what it actually looks and feels like to be a woman in the tech
        industry. Guests share their honest experiences, the ones that don't make it onto
        LinkedIn. Topics include burnout, imposter syndrome, career change, mental health,
        and building a life that works. Available on Spotify and Apple Podcasts.
      </p>
      <div class="podcast-links">
        <a class="podcast-link" href="https://open.spotify.com/show/4zFlR2qZ2jggwSp9mYrttP" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" aria-label="Listen on Spotify">Listen on Spotify</a>
        <a class="podcast-link" href="https://podcasts.apple.com/podcast/wellness-and-women-in-tech/id1680513128" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" aria-label="Listen on Apple Podcasts">Listen on Apple Podcasts</a>
      </div>
    </section>

  </div>
</BeLayout>

<style>
  .page {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin-inline: auto;
    padding: 6rem 2rem 5rem;
  }
  @media (max-width: 767px) {
    .page { padding: 5rem 1.5rem 6rem; }
  }

  /* ── atmospheric photo ─────────────────── */
  .atmospheric-photo {
    max-width: 70vh;
    margin: 5rem auto;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .atmospheric-photo img {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    display: block;
  }

  .atmospheric-photo figcaption {
    font-family: var(--font-serif-be);
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    margin-top: 0.75rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
  }

  /* ── photos ──────────────────────────── */
  .method-photo {
    width: 100%;
    max-width: 500px;
    height: auto;
    border-radius: 8px;
    display: block;
    margin: 2.5rem auto;
    aspect-ratio: 3/4;
    object-fit: cover;
    object-position: center top;
  }
  .method-photo-landscape {
    aspect-ratio: 4/3;
    max-width: 600px;
  }

  /* ── opening pull-quote ──────────────── */
  .be-hero-quote {
    font-family: var(--font-serif-be);
    font-style: italic;
    font-weight: 400;
    font-size: clamp(28px, 3.5vw, 44px);
    line-height: 1.25;
    color: var(--color-text);
    max-width: 35rem;
    margin: 0 0 2rem 0;
  }

  /* ── body prose ───────────────────────── */
  .body {
    font-family: var(--font-serif-be);
    font-weight: 400;
    font-size: 17px;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
    margin: 0 0 1.25em;
    max-width: 65ch;
  }
  .body:last-of-type { margin-bottom: 0; }

  /* ── section chrome ───────────────────── */
  .section {
    margin-top: 3rem;
    padding-top: 3rem;
    border-top: 0.5px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .section-label {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-weight: 300;
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
  }

  .section-title {
    font-family: var(--font-serif-be);
    font-weight: 400;
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 26px;
    line-height: 1.2;
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
    margin: 0 0 1.25rem;
  }

  /* ── tools list ───────────────────────── */
  .tools-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.5rem;
  }
  .tools-item {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-weight: 300;
    font-size: 14px;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    padding-left: 1rem;
    position: relative;
  }
  .tools-item::before {
    content: '—';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    font-size: 12px;
  }

  /* ── podcast ──────────────────────────── */
  .podcast-title {
    font-family: var(--font-serif-be);
    font-weight: 400;
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 22px;
    line-height: 1.2;
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
    margin: 0 0 1.25rem;
  }

  .podcast-links {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  .podcast-link {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-weight: 400;
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: opacity 200ms ease;
  }
  .podcast-link:hover { opacity: 0.75; }
</style>
